{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://leoshcn.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Alide Topp (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the pianist <b><a href=\"/wiki/Alide_Topp\" title=\"Alide Topp\">Alide Topp</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> once responded to claims that women lacked the \"biceps of a man\" for great music by stating she broke her pianos as well as any man?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alide_Topp","retrieved":1773902028452},{"title":"Tlingit (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the first writing system for <b><a href=\"/wiki/Tlingit_language\" title=\"Tlingit language\">Tlingit</a></b>, a Native American language, was based on the Cyrillic alphabet?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tlingit_language","retrieved":1773902028454},{"title":"Stardew Valley (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that some players who obtained <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Stardew_Valley\" title=\"Stardew Valley\">Stardew Valley</a></b></i> illegally were so impressed they planned to buy it?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stardew_Valley","retrieved":1773902028454},{"title":"a 1987 referendum (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/1987_Mississippi_Amendment_3\" title=\"1987 Mississippi Amendment 3\">a 1987 referendum</a></b> to repeal Mississippi's unenforceable interracial marriage ban was opposed by more than 48 percent of voters?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1987_Mississippi_Amendment_3","retrieved":1773902028456},{"title":"Clear Usui (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that VTuber <b><a href=\"/wiki/Clear_Usui\" title=\"Clear Usui\">Clear Usui</a></b> is the ambassador of Japan's satellite navigation system?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clear_Usui","retrieved":1773902028461},{"title":"Quatre instants (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <a href=\"/wiki/Kaija_Saariaho\" title=\"Kaija Saariaho\">Kaija Saariaho</a>'s <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Quatre_instants\" title=\"Quatre instants\">Quatre instants</a></b></i> have been described as \"a quasi-operatic monologue\" in \"erotic, extreme territory\"?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quatre_instants","retrieved":1773902028465},{"title":"Peter Suder (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Suder\" title=\"Peter Suder\">Peter Suder</a></b> said that the toughest basketball player he had faced was a <a href=\"/wiki/National_Football_League\" title=\"National Football League\">National Football League</a> player?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Suder","retrieved":1773902028466},{"title":"a war against Ava (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that King <a href=\"/wiki/Binnya_Ran_I\" title=\"Binnya Ran I\">Binnya Ran</a> launched <b><a href=\"/wiki/Ava%E2%80%93Hanthawaddy_War_(1430%E2%80%931431)\" title=\"Ava–Hanthawaddy War (1430–1431)\">a war against Ava</a></b> after <a href=\"/wiki/Shin_Sawbu\" title=\"Shin Sawbu\">his sister</a> fled the Ava capital?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ava%E2%80%93Hanthawaddy_War_(1430%E2%80%931431)","retrieved":1773902028467},{"title":"Courtaud (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Courtaud\" title=\"Courtaud\">Courtaud</a></b>, an infamous man-eating beast described as a \"terrible and horrible wolf\", was named for its stumpy tail?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Courtaud","retrieved":1773902028468},{"title":"Destination of the Month (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r4523569\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion\" about=\"#mwt7\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;templatestyles&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;Banner/styles.css&quot;},&quot;parts&quot;:[{&quot;template&quot;:{&quot;target&quot;:{&quot;wt&quot;:&quot;banner&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;./Template:Banner&quot;},&quot;params&quot;:{&quot;direction&quot;:{&quot;wt&quot;:&quot;left&quot;},&